  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering generally refers to financial transactions designed to conceal the origins of illegally obtained money. Legal definitions typically involve three key stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source through complex transactions\n3. Integration: Making funds appear legitimate\n\nSpecific legal definitions vary by jurisdiction, but most include:\n- Knowingly processing proceeds from criminal activity\n- Attempting to disguise the source of funds\n- Transferring or converting criminal proceeds\n- Concealing the nature, location, ownership, or control of funds\n\nPenalties can include significant fines and criminal prosecution.\n\nI want to be clear that while I can discuss this topic generally, I cannot provide advice about specific legal situations.",
